overview: The user initiated an urgent request to fix numerous issues in a pull
  request for a sleep questionnaire application, including critical security
  vulnerabilities and broken Vercel deploys. The agent adopted a systematic
  approach, starting with a thorough review of PR comments, CI logs, and
  relevant code files. Key decisions involved prioritizing a critical admin
  authentication flaw, which was resolved by implementing a secure HMAC-based
  session system. The agent also addressed several functional bugs, such as
  incorrect PDF metric calculations, inert download buttons, and issues with
  number input fields. Lint errors, initially reported by CI, were found to be
  locally resolved, prompting a careful staging and committing process to
  include only the relevant code fixes. The agent ensured all changes passed
  local lint and build checks before pushing them to the remote, resulting in a
  more secure, stable, and functional application.
